Sentencas: Protective coatings with high electrical conductivity that resist oxide scale growth are required for stainless steel interconnect materials in the long-term durable operation of solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications

Sentencas: This work evaluates the oxidation and electrical behavior of Crofer 22 APU ferritic stainless steel coated with manganese and cobalt by electrodeposition.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications

Sentencas: Isothermal and cyclic oxidation (800 A degrees C in air) tests were done to evaluate the role of the coating layer during oxidation.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications

Sentencas: Area-specific resistance (ASR) of the coated and uncoated substrates was also tested at 800 A degrees C in air.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications

Sentencas: Results show that the coating layer transforms into Mn1.5Co1.5O4 spinel during oxidation.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications

Sentencas: The mass gain and spallation indicated that the formation of Mn-Co spinel improves the high temperature oxidation.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications

Sentencas: These spinels also cause a reduction in ASR for electroplated substrates (12.42 m Omega cm(2)) as compared to uncoated ones (38.74 m Omega cm(2)) after 400 h of isothermal oxidation at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Oxidation and Electrical Behavior of a Ferritic Stainless Steel with a Mn-Co-Based Coating for SOFC Interconnect Applications
